[src:z-transform/z-transform] In example 2, the causal system yields a ROC that includes $|z|=\infty$ while the anticausal system in example 3 yields an ROC that includes ⁠ $\vert z\vert =0$ ⁠.
[src:z-transform/z-transform] In systems with multiple poles it is possible to have a ROC that includes neither $|z|=\infty$ nor ⁠ $\vert z\vert =0$ ⁠.
