[src:z-transform/z-transform] When the $x(nT)$ sequence is periodic, its DTFT is divergent at one or more harmonic frequencies, and zero at all other frequencies.
[src:z-transform/z-transform] This is often represented by the use of amplitude-variant Dirac delta functions at the harmonic frequencies.
